    <fr:route>FA-0037.xml</fr:route>
    <fr:title text="Orthogonal Complement">Orthogonal Complement</fr:title>
    <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
    <fr:date>
      <fr:year>2025</fr:year>
      <fr:month>5</fr:month>
      <fr:day>26</fr:day>
    </fr:date>
    <fr:authors />
  </fr:frontmatter>
  <fr:mainmatter>
    <fr:p>For a subset <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[S]]></fr:tex> of a <fr:link type="local" href="FA-002J.xml" addr="FA-002J" title="Hilbert Space">Hilbert space</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[H]]></fr:tex>, the orthogonal complement of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[S]]></fr:tex>, denoted <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[S^\perp ]]></fr:tex>, is defined as:</fr:p>
    <fr:p>
      <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{S^\perp  = \{y \in  H : \langle  y, x \rangle  = 0 \text { for all } x \in  S\}}]]></fr:tex>
    </fr:p>
    <fr:p>Key properties:</fr:p>
    <fr:ul><fr:li><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[S^\perp ]]></fr:tex> is always a closed <fr:link type="external" href="FA-0126">linear subspace</fr:link> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[H]]></fr:tex></fr:li>
  <fr:li><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[(S^\perp )^\perp  = \overline {\text {span}(S)}]]></fr:tex>, where <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\ \overline {\text {span}(S)}]]></fr:tex> is the <fr:link type="external" href="FA-0127">closed linear span</fr:link> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[S]]></fr:tex></fr:li>
  <fr:li>If <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[M]]></fr:tex> is a closed subspace of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[H]]></fr:tex>, then <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[H = M \oplus  M^\perp ]]></fr:tex></fr:li> (direct sum decomposition)</fr:ul>
  </fr:mainmatter>
  <fr:backmatter>
    <fr:tree toc="false" numbered="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" expanded="true" root="false" xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml">
